<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Promotion at Hay & Co
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">
<BR>
<font size=-1>
<A HREF="/appeal.html">Help fight the legal battle for free WWW links</A>
</font>
<P>
<H1>Promotion at Hay & Co
</H1>
<H2></H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.hay.zetnet.co.uk/"><img src="/haysicon/hays.gif" vspace=2 alt="Hay&Co" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=72></A>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt5.gif">
<HR>
</center>
<P>

<P>
8th January 1997
<P>
International shipping agents Hay & Company have promoted a Lerwick  lifeboatman, Iain Tulloch, to be manager of their agency division in Shetland.
<P>
Mr Tulloch (41) has been with the firm for 22 years and will take  over in April when Lindsay Aitken retires after 47 years' service with Hays.
<P>
Shetland-born Mr Tulloch is chairman of the Shetland Oil Industries  Group, a Lerwick Harbour trustee, honorary Swedish consul and a  well-known member of the Lerwick Lifeboat crew.
<P>
Founded in Lerwick in 1844, Hay & Company now have an extensive  agency business, with aircraft handling at Sumburgh Airport and busy  shipping offices in Lerwick and the tanker harbour of Sullom Voe. 
<P>
Other Hays interests include shipowning, shipbroking, stevedoring,  freight forwarding and a travel agency. They have been Lloyd's Agents  in Shetland for 135 years.
<P>



<P>
<BR clear=all>
