<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Narrow escape for salmon tender
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">
<BR>
<font size=-1>
<A HREF="/appeal.html">Help fight the legal battle for free WWW links</A>
</font>
<P>
<H1>Narrow escape for salmon tender
</H1>
<H2></H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt5.gif">
<HR>
</center>
<P>

<P>
8th January 1997
<P>
Two Shetland fish farmers and their passenger had a narrow escape  yesterday [TUES] when their boat almost capsized at the mouth of  Scalloway Harbour.
<P>
Brothers Angus and Calum Grains sent out a Mayday call when the  42-foot tender 'Celerity' took a severe list after tanks full of  salmon smolts shifted on deck.
<P>
Coastguards said the situation was so serious that the crew and a  salmon firm representative on board launched their liferaft.
<P>
The Coastguard rescue helicopter was scrambled from Sumburgh Airport  but a local fishing boat, the 'Challenge', was on the scene first and  towed the 'Celerity' and her crew safely into dock at Scalloway.
<P>




<P>
<BR clear=all>
