<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News -  Lifeboat called to burning boat
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">
<BR>
<font size=-1>
<A HREF="/appeal.html">Help fight the legal battle for free WWW links</A>
</font>
<P>
<H1> Lifeboat called to burning boat
</H1>
<H2></H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt5.gif">
<HR>
</center>
<P>

<P>
8th January 1997
<P>
Lerwick Lifeboat went to the aid of a scallop fishing boat early  yesterday [TUES] morning after a fire on board.
<P>
The two-man crew of the 30-foot 'Annie Francis' radioed for help  around 5am when their heating stove caught fire two miles east of the  uninhabited island of Noss.
<P>
The crew managed to contain the blaze with a fire extinguisher. The  lifeboat escorted them the six miles to Lerwick, where the local fire  brigade put the fire out.
<P>
No-one was hurt in the incident, which was co-ordinated by Shetland  Coastguard. The 'Annie Francis' is registered in Aberdeen but owned locally.
<P>
A few hours earlier, an ill fisherman from the Fraserburgh boat  'King's Cross' was flown to hospital in Lerwick by a Shell helicopter  from the Brent oilfield.
<P>



<P>
<BR clear=all>
