<h2>USNO RUNNING MASTER CLOCK</h2>

The <a href="http://tycho.usno.navy.mil/srss.html">U.S. Naval Obervatory</a> 
provides a running GIF clock service. The clock ticks 10 seconds. 
<br>
<B>Reload this page to restart</B>.<p>

<p>
<hr width=80%>
<p>
<centre>

<TABLE BORDER=3><TR><TH>
 Current Time
 <IMG SRC="http://tycho.usnogps.navy.mil/cgi-bin/nph-usnoclock.gif?zone=UTC;ticks=10" ALT="USNO Master Clock">
 
 </TH></TR></TABLE>


</center>
<p>
<hr width=80%><p>
The running GIF clock service is experimental. It sends about 200 bytes/sec 
while the clock is running. The U.S. Naval Observatory  cannot guarantee it will always be available. 
The running GIF clock was developed for browsers that support 'Content type: 
multipart/x-mixed-pelace'. Netscape does this correctly. Internet Explorer 3.0 
and others do not.<p> 
