<h2>1/9/96</h2>

There have now been a staggering <b>25 CONVOLVULUS HAWK-MOTHS</b> trapped in Shetland during the last few weeks, by far in excess of the 1 or 2 normally seen here in any one year!!!

<p>

The <b>KING EIDER</b> is still present between Trondra and Burra, as is the Quendale <b>CITRINE WAGTAIL</b> and the Veensgarth <b>WRYNECK</b>.

