1145: 4 female/imm Common Scoter in flight of The Sneckan, east of Nesting.<BR>
1220 - 1620: A total of 47 Harbour Horpoises seen from Dunter on a trip from Lerwick to 
Skerries and back. Main concentrations of porpoises around east Whalsay 
Holms, off Muckle Holm and between Skerries and the Skaw of Whalsay.<BR>
1135 - 1640: 448 Eiders counted by Martin Heubeck of SOTEAG in scattered flocks between 
Hoo Stack and Skerries. Main concentrations north of Skerries.

