<A NAME="one"></a><BR>
<A HREF="#Top"><IMG SRC="/pics/up.gif"></A><BR>
<CENTER><H2>Section One - Guidelines if YOU'VE been affected</H2>
<H3>Slick Operators - <STRONG><I>The Shetland News</I></STRONG> spill survival guide</H3></CENTER>
<P>
<P> <STRONG>Do's and dont's for Small Businesses affected by the 'Sea Empress' disaster </STRONG>
<P>(The writer runs a small business in Shetland and survived the Braer) 

<UL>
<P><LI>1 <STRONG>Keep</STRONG> a very detailed daily diary of the spill as it affects your business. Note down ALL the hours you spend dealing with things connected with the spill - and what you would normally have been doing. 
<P><LI>2 <STRONG>Look after</STRONG> your customers. You will need them after all this is over. Send them daily bulletins explaining honestly what is happening to your business and why. 
<P><LI>3 <STRONG>Do NOT sign</STRONG> anything, particularly from the polluters or their insurers. NEVER take their advice. Get your own independent advisers. 
<P><LI>4 <STRONG>Remember</STRONG> - you are rightfully claiming what has been taken from you. It's the POLLUTER'S duty to make you whole again. He wants evidence, so write down every expense the spill has caused. 
<P><LI>5 <STRONG>YOU</STRONG> are in the right. Stick together with your business friends and your trade or professional association. If you fall out, only the polluter will benefit. 
<P><LI>6 <STRONG>Look after</STRONG> your staff. They will have compensation claims too. If you have to lay them off, tell them in writing why, so they can use it in evidence to support their claims. 
<P><LI>7 <STRONG>Ask</STRONG> your customers to fax you their reasons if they cancel orders. This is VERY important. 
<P><LI>8 <STRONG>Never</STRONG> make unsubstantiated compensation claims. 
<P><LI>9 <STRONG>Remember</STRONG> - this has happened before. You are not alone. In Brittany, Alaska, Spain and Shetland you have thousands of friends you haven't met yet. They can and WILL help you. 
</UL>

<P>


<CENTER>
<img width=75% height=3 src="/pics/thinbar.gif">
</CENTER>

<A NAME="two"></a>
<BR>
<A HREF="#Top"><IMG SRC="/pics/up.gif"></A>
