<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News - Big liner calls at Lerwick
   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1> Big liner calls at Lerwick
   </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>

8th August 1996
<P>
The largest cruise liner to call at Shetland this year spent yesterday (WED) in Lerwick Harbour.
<P>
P&O's 44,000 tonne 'Royal Princess' was on passage from Rosyth to Iceland.
<P>
The big visitor was the 30th liner in what harbour officials believe will be a record season.
<P>
Lerwick already welcomes more cruise passengers than any other Scottish port. With fishing and oil-related trade in the doldrums, the harbour trust is running a publicity campaign to attract more tourist business to the picturesque port. 




<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

Words strictly Copyright of Shetland News Agency, 1996.
<BR>
Pictures strictly Copyright of Force 10 Photos, 1996.

