<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Seaman flown to hospital in Lerwick

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Seaman flown to hospital in Lerwick
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
8th November 1996
<P>
A Shell helicopter last night (THURS) flew an injured Portuguese  seaman to hospital in Lerwick after a fall on a supply ship 100 miles  north-east of Shetland.
<P>
The un-named casualty suffered a broken wrist and bruising in the  accident aboard the 'Stirling Clyde', alongside the Brent Delta oil  platform, a Shell spokesman said. 
<P>
A doctor from the 'Safe Gothia' accommodation rig flew to the ship  and gave first aid before taking the patient back to the rig. A Bell  212 chopper later transferred him to the Gilbert Bain Hospital,  landing just before 11pm.
<P>









<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

