<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News -  Trawler frees propeller under tow

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>   Trawler frees propeller under tow
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
7th November 1996
<P>
A Shetland trawler under tow by the Aith lifeboat last night (WED)  managed to clear a net fouling her propeller in rough seas 20 miles  out in the Atlantic.
<P>
Six hours into the tow, the 110-foot-long 'Santos' reported that she  was able to continue unaided to the port of Scalloway.
<P>
Lifeboatmen in the west Shetland village of Aith had put to sea  shortly before noon, after the four-man crew of the trawler radioed for help.
<P>
Last night (WED) the weary lifeboatmen were punching into a strong  north-easterly wind on their way back to base, as the 'Santos' headed  for harbour to check for damage.
<P>










<P>
<BR clear=all>
