<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Hydro blacks out Bressay and TV - yet again

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Hydro blacks out Bressay and TV - yet again
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
5th November 1996
<P>
TV reception in Shetland was blacked out last night (TUES) for the  second time in three days when a Hydro Electric transformer blew up  on the island of Bressay.
<P>
Bressay Councillor Tavish Scott (Liberal Democrat) said: 'This is not  good enough. I want an explanation from the Hydro and an assurance  that they're doing everything possible to make sure this doesn't happen again.'
<P>
On Friday night a power cut blacked out Bressay and the main BBC and  ITV transmitters on the island's Ward Hill for over three hours.
<P>
Last Christmas parts of Shetland were without power for five days  after a blizzard brought down power lines but last night's weather,  although bad, was not exceptional by Shetland standards.
<P>
As high winds and rain swept over Bressay (pop. 370) one angry  islander said: 'This is a joke. I want compensation. What's it going  to be like when the real winter weather starts?'
<P>
Power was restored after three hours.
<P>









<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

Words strictly Copyright of Shetland News Agency, 1996.
<BR>
Pictures strictly Copyright of Force 10 Photos, 1996.

