<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Flying pumps save trawler

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Flying pumps save trawler
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>

<P>
3rd November 1996
<P>
A Fraserburgh fishing boat with seven crew on board made it safely  into port  this morning (SUN) after the Shetland Coastguard  helicopter helped prevent a sinking.
<P>
The trawler 'Utility' (FR 393) radioed for help late on Saturday  night when she sprang a leak in her engine room, 70 miles south of  Sumburgh Head, Shetland.
<P>
After the helicopter Oscar Charlie lowered two mobile pumps to the  boat just before midnight, the crew managed to bring the flooding  under control and headed for Fraserburgh.
<P>








<P>
<BR clear=all>
