<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News -  New ferry skipper appointed

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>   New ferry skipper appointed
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
2nd November 1996
<P>
The island of Foula has a new ferry skipper, the day after a new Foula ferry arrived in Shetland.
<P>
SIC yesterday (FRI) appointed 35-year-old Captain Andrew Horley from Holyhead, Anglesey, after interviewing suitably qualified candidates.
<P>
Capt Horley and his wife Denise, a nurse, have two  children aged two and three.
<P>
The new Skipper is expected to arrive in Foula and take command of the 38-foot 'New Advance' next month.
<P>
<A HREF="/headline/here/here.html">See our story about the arrival of the new ferry, yesterday</A>








<P>
<BR clear=all>
