<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - What's in this week's Shetland Times...

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  What's in this week's Shetland Times...
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
2nd November 1996
<P>
(Don't panic - this is what's in the printed version. We're not  allowed to look at the online edition or refer you to it)
<P>
The paper leads with more details of the controversy over council  chief executive Malcolm Green's purchase of 25,000 pounds' worth of  anti-surveillance equipment for Lerwick Town Hall.
<P>
Other stories include:
<P>
* Increasing evidence that Shell will keep Unst airport open as a  diversion for offshore helicopter flights, saving several of the jobs  lost when Chevron pulled out;
<P>
* A computer error at the Co-op Superstore in Lerwick which delayed  up to four weeks in charging Switch-card holders for their groceries  - with annoying and embarrassing results;
<P>
* Shetland Oil Industries Group is sending a delegation to the  Falkland Islands, where offshore oil exploration is hotting up;
<P>
* BP's new 'floater' - the 'Petrojarl Foinaven' production, storage  and loading ship - is on her way from a Spanish shipyard at last,  bound for the new oilfield 100 miles west of Shetland.
<P>
What's not in this week's Shetland Times (in either the print or, so  we're told, the electronic edition):
<P>
*  Many letters from readers complaining about The Shetland Times'  legal action against The Shetland News;
<P>
*  Any mention of the fact that The Shetland Times has not accepted a  peace offer from The Shetland News;
<P>
*  Any mention of the links to Shetland Times pages being made by  websites all over the world. Will there be many other court actions? We  think we should be told.
<P>









<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

