<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - 'Positive' growth in tourist trade

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  'Positive' growth in tourist trade
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>

<P>
1st November 1996
<P>
Tourism in Shetland shows 'positive and solid' growth as the industry  claws back the trade lost by bad publicity after the Braer tanker  disaster, according to the islands' tourism director, Maurice Mullay.
<P>
Mr Mullay told the first annual meeting of the new <A HREF="http://www.shetland-tourism.co.uk/">Shetland Islands  Tourism</A> there was a seven per cent increase this year in inquiries  about holidays in Shetland.
<P>
'Members reports on the past season showed encouraging results,' he  said, particularly in the rural areas and offlying islands of  Shetland. 'Visitor numbers by air and sea have increased but fewer  yachts visited because of the bad weather this season. An increase in  cruise liner passengers  was a boost to local businesses.
<P>
'Whale watching was popular and the sightings attracted excellent  press reports,' Mr Mullay told the meeting. 'Our public relations operation   continued to give outstanding value, with media coverage valued at  hundreds of thousands of pounds.'
<P>
The meeting elected Peter Tulloch of Kirkhouse Chalets, Bixter, as  chairman of the new statutory tourism body, Shetland Islands Tourism.  Julie Jenner, who operates an award-winning bed & breakfast  establishment at Skellister, South Nesting, was appointed vice-chairman.
<P>
New directors joining the SIT board were Laurence Tulloch of Yell,  representing the North Isles, and Arthur Williamson, representing  Scalloway, Burra and Trondra.
<P>
Mrs Jenner paid tribute to the dedication and efforts of the  directors over the past year, and regret at losing Peter Guy who had  been a keen and enthusiastic chairman. Mr Guy left the islands last  month. Mrs Jenner also paid tribute to the hard work and long hours  worked by the tourist office's pleasant and efficient staff.
<P>









<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

Words strictly Copyright of Shetland News Agency, 1996.
<BR>
Pictures strictly Copyright of Force 10 Photos, 1996.

