<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Jailed for indecent assault on girl

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Jailed for indecent assault on girl
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>

<P>
25th October 1996
<P>
A 62-year-old Orkney man who admitted indecently assaulting a  12-year-old girl was sentenced at Lerwick Sherriff Court to six  months in prison yesterday (THU)
<P>
John Robert Tulloch, known as 'Orkney John', of 1 Brakefield Cresent,  Haroldswick, Unst, Shetland, pleaded guilty of three charges, all  involving indecency.
<P>
The most serious incident happened on the evening of the October 4 in front of Lerwick's Garrison Theatre, where he seized hold of a  12-year-old girl and attempted to expose himself.
<P>
He also admitted indecently assaulting a woman at her house near the theatre later the same evening and being guilty of a similar charge  arising from an incident in the island of Unst on April 29 this year.
<P>
Solicitor Michael Inkster said that there would be no repeat, due to  the fact that Mr Tulloch was now on his way to being able to 'control  his drinking'. There had been a difficult phase in his marriage and  he now sought marriage guidance, he said. He had the support of his wife.
<P>
Mr Inkster asked Sheriff Colin Scott Mackenzie not to be too hard on  his client.
<P>
The Sheriff jailed Tulloch for six months, saying he had 'no other option'.
<P>







<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

