<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Call for Crown to hand over the seabed

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Call for Crown to hand over the seabed
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>

<P>
24th October 1996
<P>
The Crown Estate should hand over the inshore seabed to local people,  the Shetland Movement said yesterday (WED).
<P>
Jack Burgess, chairman of the party seeking more home rule for the  islands, said the seabed should be 'under democratic control' and  managed 'in accordance with the wishes of the local community'.
<P>
Commenting on the continuing rental disputes between the Crown Estate  and several committees running small boat marinas in Shetland, Mr  Burgess said: 'They're really community activities and they shouldn't  be commercially rented.
<P>
'The Shetland Movement has decided to press for the ownership of the  inshore seabed to be transferred from the Crown Estate to local  public ownership,' he said.
<P>
In Shetland such a change would be 'appropriate', because the council  already had powers to control what went on in coastal waters.
<P>







<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

