<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//Netscape Comm. Corp.//DTD HTML//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News -  Full to bursting at the Fish Fiesta

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>   Full to bursting at the Fish Fiesta
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
17th October 1996
<P>
The 'best meal of the year' was a sell-out in Shetland last night  (WED) as gourmet supporters of the Fishermen's Mission crowded into  the North Atlantic Fisheries College at Scalloway.
<P>
The finest Shetland seafood made a spectacular buffet for diners at  the annual mission fund-raiser, sponsored by fish farmers, fishermen,  fish processors and the college.
<P>
Mission superintendent Cliff Powell said the reputation of the 'Fish  Fiesta' was such that nearly all the 90 tickets sold within 36 hours,  at 12.50 pounds a go.
<P>
'They say it's the best meal of the year,' said Mr Powell, who  recently succeeded Superintendent Ian Munro as the 'Mission Man' in  the islands. 'We're very grateful for the generous support of our  sponsors and guests.'
<P>
The Royal National Mission to Deep Sea Fishermen is making a special  fund-raising effort this year, to help pay for upgrading its own  kitchens at the Mission building in Harbour Street, Lerwick, a  popular meeting-and-eating place for fishermen and the general public alike.
<P>








<P>
