<TITLE>Shetland News -  Whalsay youth club goes on-line

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>   Whalsay youth club goes on-line
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
11th October 1996
<P>
The Livister Youth Club in the island of Whalsay has joined the  growing number of Shetland organisations using e-mail and the World Wide Web.
<P>
Youth leader John Dally said yesterday (THURS): 'We think we're the  first youth club in Shetland to be online.'
<P>
With access via Zetnet, Shetland's nationwide Internet service  provider, the club has its own mailbox, <A HREF="mailto:lyc@zetnet.co.uk">lyc@zetnet.co.uk</A>. 
<P>
Mr Dally said: 'Members will be able to log on to the Internet and  hope to make contact with young people around the world. As we  develop expertise, we plan to devise a home page of our own.'
<P>








<P>
