<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News -  Publican hopes to avoid planners' closure order

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>   Publican hopes to avoid planners' closure order
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
10th October 1996
<P>
Councillors wearing their planning hats yesterday (WED) voted to  close down a Shetland country pub which they approved last year with  their licensing board hats on.
<P>
Undismayed, Clive Mouat of the Pierhead Restaurant and Bar in the  picture-postcard village of Voe said he would put in a new planning  application to stay open.
<P>
Depute planning director Alastar Hamilton told councillors Mr Mouat  had not replied to letters pointing out that he did not have planning  permission for a pub, only for a restaurant and guest house.
<P>
The problems were unauthorised change of use of the building and not  enough car parking on a narrow road through the village, Mr Hamilton  said. He recommend enforcement action to close the public bar. 
<P>
Local councillor Maisie Colligan told the meeting: 'I can't see a way  round this .. I feel quite sad about it.' The pub was 'a very popular  place' but she felt she had no option to moving for enforcement action.
<P>
Councillors, including those who sit on the licensing board, the  agreed without a vote to give Mr Mouat a month to shut his public bar. 
<P>
Committee chairman Bill Manson said the Pierhead's public bar licence  was 'a quite separate matter' and should not be discussed at a  planning meeting.
<P>
Mr Mouat said he had thought he did have the proper permits: 'I'm not  wanting to fight with anybody about this. I spoke to the planning  department on Monday and showed them my plans for the car park on the  sea frontage. I'm sure I can satisfy their concerns.' He would be  applying shortly for new planning consents.
<P>

<P>








<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

Words strictly Copyright of Shetland News Agency, 1996.
<BR>
Pictures strictly Copyright of Force 10 Photos, 1996.

