<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News -  Christine is the isles' top writer

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>   Christine is the isles' top writer
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
8th October 1996
<P>
A Shetland-born poet with an increasing national reputation has won  the islands' top writing prize.
<P>
Christine De Luca, nee Pearson, a former pupil of Anderson High  School, Lerwick, was the judges' unanimous choice for the 1996  Shetland Arts Trust Literary Award, with her book of poems 'Voes and Sound'.
<P>
Ms De Luca, a graduate of Edinburgh University, qualified as a  geography teacher and now works for the Scottish Examination Board.
<P>
Her former English teacher, John Graham, joint editor of the literary  quarterly 'New Shetlander' which regularly publishes Ms De Luca's  work, said yesterday (MON): 'This is one of the best collections of  poetry to come out of Shetland for 20 or 30 years.
<P>
'Christine was a very bright, sparkling pupil, a very talented young  lady. That talent is now maturing,' he said.
<P>
The judges were particularly impressed by by Ms De Luca's equal  facility in English and her native dialect.
<P>
She said she was 'absolutely delighted' that, unlike the prophet in  the  old saying, she had been accepted in her own country: 'It's very  special,' she said.  She is currently working on a second collection  of poems. Like the first, it will celebrate the Shetland landscape  and her favourite places on the west mainland of the islands.
<P>
Mr Graham himself was voted BBC Radio Shetland Playwright of the Year  for his play 'A Bit o' Laand', exploring the fierce attachment of old  people to their crofts.
<P>
Shetland's Young Writer of the Year was 14-year-old Floortje  Robertson from the village of Walls, with 'Countdown for Luke', the  tale of a space cadet who falls foul of a crew of nasty aliens.
<P>








<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

