<TITLE>Shetland News - Remanded on indecency charges

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Remanded on indecency charges
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
<P>
8th October 1996
<P>
A 62-year-old man was remanded in custody at Lerwick Sheriff Court  yesterday (MON) after admitting indecently assaulting a 12-year-old girl.
<P>
The court heard that John Robert Tulloch, 1 Brakefield Crescent,  Haroldswick, Unst, Shetland, seized hold of the girl outside  Lerwick's Garrison Theatre on Friday evening and attempted to expose himself.
<P>
Tulloch, known as 'Orkney John', also admitted indecently assaulting  a woman at a house near the theatre later the same evening.
<P>
The court deferred sentence to October 24, pending social inquiry,  community service and victim reports.
<P>
Earlier on Friday, Tulloch had been released on bail pending a trial,  after appearing in the Lerwick court to deny indecently assaulting a  woman in the island of Unst on April 29.
<P>
He admitted five previous convictions, none involving indecent assault.
<P>









<P>
<BR clear=all>
