<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News - Steward dies aboard 'St Sunniva'

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1> Steward dies aboard 'St Sunniva'
   </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>



28th September 1996
<P>
A crewman on the P&O ferry 'St Sunniva' died yesterday morning (FRI) while on passage from Aberdeen to Shetland.
<P>
John Russell Slater (40), 1 Sanquhar Mains, Forres, Morayshire, was a steward on the 4,000 tonne ship. 
<P>
Police said Mr Slater's colleagues became concerned at his condition when they went to waken him in his cabin shortly before six in the morning.
<P>
The captain immediately ordered extra speed and docked ahead of schedule at Lerwick, where a doctor and an ambulance were waiting at the quayside. But Mr Slater was pronounced dead just after 7.30am.
<P>
Shetland police said they understood he was a single man. There were no suspicious circumstances but a report on the sudden death would be sent to the procurator fiscal.





<P>
<BR clear=all>
