<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News - Airlift to hospital in Lerwick

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1> Airlift to hospital in Lerwick
   </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>


28th September 1996
<P>
The Banff-registered fishing boat 'Wayfarer' sent out an emergency call in the early hours of yesterday (FRI) when a crewman suffered suspected appendicitis.
<P>
The Shetland Coastguard rescue helicopter flew 100 miles to the ship and winched up the casualty in high winds and heavy seas. He was later landed at the Gilbert Bain Hospital in Lerwick for treatment.
<P>
The crewman has not been named.
<P>
The 'Wayfarer' was on standby duty alongside the drilling rig 'Maersk Vinlander' in the East Shetland Basin oilfields.
<P>
The incident was the 57th callout this year for the Sumburgh rescue chopper operated by Bristows for the Coastguards.






<P>
<BR clear=all>
