<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News - Svein-Ove faces severe gale Force 9 tonight

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1>  Svein-Ove faces severe gale Force 9 tonight
  </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>
26th September 1996
<P>
A change in the wind allowed Norwegian rower Svein Ove Ask to make  some headway to the eastwards yesterday (WED) on his attempt to row  alone from Shetland to Norway.
<P>
But he was still way off course after three days of adverse weather  and faces another gale at sea tonight (THURS).
<P>
Although he has rowed an estimated 75 miles since leaving Lerwick on  Sunday, Mr Ask's last reported position was only 20 miles north-east  of the Muckle Flugga lighthouse at the northern tip of Shetland. He  still has 160 miles to go.
<P>
Yesterday morning he radioed Shetland Coastguards to say all was well  after a night of high winds and heavy seas.
<P>
Last night the wind eased and veered south-westerly, allowing him to  row due east. 
<P>
The offshore marine forecast for tonight shows renewed southerly  gales, with gusts to severe gale force nine and waves up to 25 feet high. 
<P>
<P>
<a href="/svein/svein.html">Follow Svein Ove Ask rowing to Norway with the Shetland News</A>








<P>
<BR clear=all>
