<HEAD>
<TITLE>Shetland News - Councillor Peter Guy resigns 

   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">

<P>
<H1> Councillor Peter Guy resigns 
   </H1>
<H2>    </H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt8.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt0.gif">
<HR>
<P>
</center>


24th September 1996
<P>
A Shetland councillor last night (MON) resigned his seat because he is moving to North Yorkshire.
<P>
Councillor Peter Guy, who was widowed last year, said he had 'a great love for the islands' and deciding about his future had been very hard: 'It's probably one of the most difficult decisions I've ever taken in my life,' he said.
<P>
Mr Guy, who hails originally from Cornwall, won the Mid and South Yell seat as an independent at a by-election in 1993 and was re-elected unopposed the following year. He is chairman of the council's Leisure and Recreation Committee, and also chairs the islands' licensing board and tourist authority.
<P>
Mr Guy and his late wife Christine, a much-loved music teacher in the island of Yell, first came to Shetland more than 20 years ago when he was posted as an air force officer to the RAF Saxa Vord radar station in the island of Unst.
<P>
On leaving the RAF, Mr Guy worked for BP's Sullom Voe oil terminal, serving as the company's Shetland press officer for many years.
<P>
A great outdoors enthusiast, he is well known in the islands as author of the 'Walking the Coastline of Shetland' guidebooks. 
<P>
In a letter of resignation, Mr Guy said he would cease to be a councillor from September 30, but would return to Shetland on holiday as often as he could.
<P>
Mr Guy's council ward is due to be amalgamated with neighbouring North Yell at the next council elections in May 1999.
<P>
There is speculation that retired council leisure director John P. Nicolson may be asked to stand at the by-election caused by Mr Guy's departure.






<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

