<H2> 
Cruise in Style to the Northern Lands  </center>  </H2>
<CENTER><img src="pnostrip2.gif"></CENTER>


<CENTER><H3>      </H3></CENTER>

<P>
There's only one way to travel to the Northern Isles of Orkney and Shetland and that's the natural way - by sea.
<P><A HREF="clair.jpg"><IMG SRC="clairs.jpg" ALIGN=left HSPACE=5 border=0></A>
Your holiday starts from the moment you step on board one of our fine vessels in Aberdeen or Scrabster.  With the excitement rising as the panorama of the islands unfolds before you, a fascinating new world awaits that is miles apart from the hustle and bustle of everyday life.
<P>
On all our vessels a warm welcome awaits you from our friendly staff and you will also find their attention to your individual requirements refreshing - the nicest way to start your holiday.
<P><A HREF="stclairreception.jpg"><IMG SRC="stclairreceptions.jpg" ALIGN=left HSPACE=5 border=0></A>
On board St Clair or St Sunniva you will find first-class restaurants, grill-rooms, gift shops, comfortable cabins, most with en suite facilities, feature films and entertainment in the bars and lounges.  St Ola on the Scrabster - Stromness crossing offers grill room, gift shop, children's play area, bar and lounge facilities.
<P><A HREF="sunniva.jpg"><IMG SRC="sunnivas.jpg" ALIGN=right HSPACE=5 border=0></A>
Whether you choose some adventurous island-hopping, a delightful mini-cruise, an inclusive hotel holiday excursion or simply a day trip then P&O Scottish Ferries has got something to offer - you will find full details in the following pages.
<P>
Why not sail, on during the summer, to Scandinavia - our service from Aberdeen and Lerwick to Bergen in Norway widens your horizons and provides new and exciting holiday and car touring opportunities for our passengers.
<BR clear=all>
<P>

