<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>P&O Scottish Ferries - </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="seaback2.jpg">
<center>


<IMG SRC="pnomainlogoblack.gif" align=center>

<H2>Norwegian Adventure
   </center>  </H2>
<CENTER><img src="pnostrip2.gif"></CENTER>


<CENTER><H3>      </H3></CENTER>

<P><A HREF="houses.jpg"><IMG SRC="housess.jpg" ALIGN=right HSPACE=5 border=0></A>
Sailing to Northern Lands is an exciting adventure!  Every Saturday during June July and August our MV St Clair sails direct from Lerwick in Shetland to Bergen, Norway's most special city situated in the west amongst spectacular mountain scenery - and gateway to the fjords.
<P><A HREF="lehmkuhl.jpg"><IMG SRC="lehmkuhls.jpg" ALIGN=left HSPACE=5 border=0></A>
This unique Scottish Connection sailing from Aberdeen, via the Shetland Islands, to Norway provides the stepping stones to a holiday you will never forget.
<P>
You can leave Aberdeen at 1800 hours on a Friday and be in Bergen by midnight on Saturday, or you can stop off in Shetland and carry on to Norway the next weekend and still benefit from the special rates.
<P>
On the return journey an early morning departure from Bergen on Sunday sees you back in Aberdeen at 0800 hours Monday morning having stopped off in Shetland on the way.
<P>
Why not sail from Aberdeen or Scrabster to Orkney, Orkney to Shetland, then on to Bergen.  Whatever your chosen route to these Northern Lands we will be pleased to make all your travel arrangements for you.
<P>

<CENTER><H2>Aberdeen - Lerwick - Bergen</H2>

