<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Lerwick Harbour Trust - Home Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFEF2">
<center>
<IMG SRC="lhtlogo.gif">

<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<H1>Fishing out of Lerwick Harbour
</H1>
<H2>
at the Centre of Europe's Richest Grounds
</H2>

</center>
<CENTER><img width=600 height=3 src="lhtstrip.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<STRONG>Four Hundred Years in the Business</STRONG>
<P><A HREF="albertbuilding.jpg"><img src="albertbuildings.jpg" align=right border=0 hspace=10 vspace=5></A>
Lerwick Harbour started life as a fishing port four centuries ago and is poised to strengthen its position in the next century as one of Britain's premier fishing ports.
<P>
Lerwick Harbour Trust, formed in 1877, has invested in new quays, sheltered docks, processing factories, net-handling areas and a temperature-controlled fishmarket, to make the port's facilities second to none. 
<P>


<br clear=all>
<P>
<STRONG>Never closed</STRONG>
<P>
Many ports have access problems in bad weather and low tides - not Lerwick. The approaches are well-lit with continuous, computerised radar cover. Pilots and tugs are available at any time. You can enter Lerwick's harbour of refuge in any weather, all-year round, day or night - there are two entrances and the tidal range is only 2.5 metres. Alongside, most berths have potable water, with mobile cranes, pumps, generators and specialist equipment on 24-hour call. Lerwick offers comprehensive repairs, maintenance, bunkering and stores around the clock.

<P><P><A HREF="office.jpg"><img src="offices.jpg" align=left border=0 hspace=10 vspace=5></A><P>
There is a slipway and floating dry-dock with full engineering backup for fishing vessels of up to 2,750 tonnes. The port has all agency services, brokerage and full Customs cover. If you are making a crew change, there are fast frequent daily air services to the UK mainland as well as regular overnight ferries to Aberdeen. More and more mainland boats are using Lerwick as a winter base. Rest and recreation facilities are first-class. In emergencies, few ports in the far north are as well equipped as Lerwick, with its high-speed RNLI lifeboat, Coastguard station, the search-and-rescue helicopter based at Sumburgh and a modern general hospital. 
<br clear=all>
<P>
<STRONG>At the Centre of Things</STRONG>
<P>
Lerwick is the fishing port at the centre of every North Sea and North Atlantic fisherman's charts. The harbour welcomes over 2,500 fishing vessels a year - not counting the local fleet - and numbers are growing as more and more skippers decide that Lerwick makes commercial sense for them. When you are not fishing your boat is eating up money, so it makes sense to use a base which minimises steaming time to and from the fishing grounds - and where specialists can get you back to sea quickly if you suffer a breakdown.


<P>
<STRONG>Lerwick - for the White Fish Fleet</STRONG>
<P><P><A HREF="unload.jpg"><img src="unloads.jpg" align=right border=0 hspace=10 vspace=5></A><P>
With markets five mornings a week and overnight fridge-freight sailings to the Scottish mainland, your catch reaches mainland and Shetland customers in prime condition. Lerwick's new fish market is one of the most modern in the UK, meeting the latest temperature control and hygiene regulations. The port has a high capacity ice plant with its own quay, supplying boats on demand, night and day. Onshore there are extensive white fish processing factories operated to the highest standards. The harbour has shelter for large numbers of trawlers and seiners in adverse weather. 


<br clear=all>
<P>
<STRONG>Lerwick - for the Pelagic Fleet</STRONG>
<P>
The port's all-weather anchorages are the centre of a huge trans-shipment operation for herring and mackerel. Specialist operators provide full agency and consular services with stores, ship tenders, bunker fuel and waste disposal available at all hours.

<P>
On shore, the Shetland Catch factory has new equipment for speedy discharge of your catch. There are deep-water berths to load reefer ships trading world-wide.

<P><A HREF="nets.jpg"><img src="netss.jpg" align=left border=0 hspace=10 vspace=5></A>
At Dales Voe, the largest vessels can lie alongside the quay which has a minimum water depth of 12.5 metres.

<P>
A large fish-meal and oil factory lies on the eastern shore of the harbour, handling fish wastes and industrial species.

<P>
Suppliers of refrigeration gases and spares for the pelagic fleet are based on the dockside.

<P>
<STRONG>Repairs and Maintenance for the Fleet</STRONG>
<P>
When something goes wrong, you do not have to waste time steaming back to mainland Scotland or Norway for repairs. The nearest slipway and dock are right here in Lerwick. 'If you bend it, Lerwick can mend it'. Experienced, skilled people will turn out at short notice around the clock to work on your problem, whether it's mechanical, electrical or electronic.

<P>
Specialist firms offer services like these up to, and beyond, mainland standards of quality and reliability:

<UL>
<P><P><A HREF="welder.jpg"><img src="welders.jpg" align=right border=0 hspace=10></A><P>
<LI>	Repairs, maintenance and modifications to hulls, deck machinery , fishing gear, marine engines, refrigeration plant, electrical gear, navigation equipment, electronics and telecommunications.

<P>
<LI>	Net-mending, handling, stacking and manufacture.

<P>
<LI>	Wire-rigging, shipchandlery.

<P><LI>	Divers, shipwrights and marine surveyors.

<P>
</UL>
<br clear=all>
When work is over, Lerwick is a great place to relax and have fun after a rough trip - maybe at the Fishermens' Mission, one of the best in Britain, or in cheerful waterfront bars, good restaurants and cafes.
<P>
Lerwick has the best leisure facilities of any town of its size in Scotland, including a new swimming pool, games hall and sports pitches.
<P>
If you are fishing in the northern grounds, it makes sense to use this convenient international port.  We will be delighted to welcome you to our growing fleet of satisfied customers.  

<P>
If, after looking at the other pages, you want to know more about Britain's Top Port, or discuss any detailed requirements in confidence, please <A HREF="mailto:lkharbour@lht.zetnet.co.uk">email us</A> today.
<P>


<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<CENTER><img width=600 height=3 src="lhtstrip.gif"></CENTER>
