<HEAD>
<TITLE>Lerwick Harbour Trust</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFEF2">
<center>
<IMG SRC="lhtlogo.gif">

<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<P>

<h1>Welcome to 'Britain's Top Port'</h1>
</CENTER>
<CENTER><img width=600 height=3 src="lhtstrip.gif"></CENTER>


<P><CENTER>
<H1>
Lerwick Harbour
</H1>
<H2>
Shetland's Front Door
</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>

Lerwick is Shetlands main commercial port, equipped for fast, efficient handling of passengers, vehicles, containers, ro-ro freight, general, bulk and specialised cargo.
<P>
A large, deep, sheltered anchorage with good holding ground is available in all weathers. Buoyage and navigational aids are first class and meet new international standards. Channels in the North Harbour and North Entrance have been deepened, to meet the demand from increased traffic and the trend to bigger ships.
<P><A HREF="clair.jpg"><IMG SRC="clairs.jpg" ALIGN=left HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 BORDER=0></A>
People and their goods have been landing on the western shores of Bressay Sound ever since the <A HREF="http://www.shetland-tourism.co.uk/vikings/vikings.html">Vikings</A> discovered this superb natural harbour over a thousand years ago.
<P>
The Vikings had to get their feet wet coming ashore and Lerwicks first docks were not built until the early 19th century. But modern passengers on the <A HREF="http://www.shetland-news.co.uk/websites/pno/">P&O ferries</A> from Aberdeen, Orkney and Norway are welcomed in a purpose-built terminal at Holmsgarth Quay.
<P>
The terminals two roll-on/roll-off berths handle most of Shetlands imports and exports. The development is central to Lerwick Harbour Trusts major investments along the two-mile waterfront over the past 20 years.
<P>
Nearby, the trust has built a new quay, dedicated to conventional lift-on/lift-off cargo handling. <A HREF="http://www.zetnet.co.uk/shetnews/oil/oil.html">Oilfield supply</A> vessels can trans-ship cargoes at Lerwicks service base quays, minimising haulage costs.
<P><A HREF="barge.jpg"><IMG SRC="barges.jpg" ALIGN=right HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 BORDER=0></A>
Backing up the dockside service are experienced local haulage firms, Lloyds and other <A HREF="http://www.hay.zetnet.co.uk/">ships agents</A>, shipbrokers and Department of Transport surveyors. There is full Customs & Excise cover, plus <A HREF="http://www.shetland-news.co.uk/websites/lht/information/phonenos.html">consulates</A> for major European maritime nations, and interpreters on request.
<P>
Lerwick is also the terminal for <A HREF="http://www.zetnet.co.uk/shetnews/tourism/time.html">Shetland Islands Councils</A> busiest ro-ro ferry. The Leirna runs hourly to the island of Bressay, which shelters the harbour from easterly winds. 

<P>
Beyond Bressay is the National Nature Reserve island of Noss, served by the Noss Sound ferry from May to August. In summer, two boats run daily birdwatching excursions to Noss from Lerwicks Victoria Pier. 
<P>
<STRONG>The Best Recommendation </STRONG>
<P><A HREF="2entrance.jpg"><IMG SRC="2entrances.jpg" ALIGN=left HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 BORDER=0></A>
Lerwick Harbours satisfied customers include <A HREF="http://www.shetland-news.co.uk/websites/pno/">P&O Scottish Ferries</A>, Shetland Line, the Royal Navy and major cruise ship operators.
<P>
Overnight passenger-cargo sailings run all year round to Aberdeen, with two calls a week at our neighbouring Orkney Islands. Shetland Line have a twice-weekly conventional freight service to the mainland.
<P>
In summer theres a weekly connection with Scandinavia - the P&O Scottish Ferries ship St Clair links Lerwick with Bergen in Norway, making us Britains most northerly international terminal for scheduled passenger/cargo services.
<P>
International trade goes on all year, with regular cargo sailings, by inducement, to Scandinavia, the Baltic, Channel ports, the Mediterranean and even Japan - where prime <A HREF="http://www.zetnet.co.uk/smoke/">Shetland seafood</A> is in great demand.
<P>
Thousands of masters and their crews have been impressed by the service at Lerwick Harbour. We think youll be pleasantly surprised too, and we look forward to doing business with you. Why not <A HREF="mailto:lkharbour@lht.zetnet.co.uk">Email us</A> today?


<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<CENTER><img width=600 height=3 src="lhtstrip.gif"></CENTER>
