<BODY><H1><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/btn6.gif" ALIGN="TOP">  EuroData<SUP>&#174;</SUP>
for Windows<SUP>&#174;</SUP></H1>
<H4><BIG>The first personal itinerary planner designed especially for the
online traveler! </BIG> </H4><IMG
SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/rrtrk.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H4> EuroData makes European travel planning point-and-click, drag-and-drop
easy.  It's simple to use, yet sophisticated enough for the real-world
complexities of travel.  <B>EuroData</B> is about designing <I>your</I> travel
<I>your</I> way... and making the most of every day &amp; dollar.  It's
<U>must-have software</U> for anyone planning travel by PC.  The best part is,
<B>EuroData for Windows</B> is <I>free</I> -- you can
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ppdown1.htm">download it right here</A>, right
now. </H4>
<P><B>(If you prefer, you can also
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/orders.htm">order EuroData on 3.5&quot; disk</A>
for a nominal shipping &amp; handling charge.)</B></P>
<H4><I>Don't mistake this for a crippled demo or cheap knockoff.</I>  We think

<BIG>EuroData for Windows</BIG>  may be the most powerful, full-featured
personal travel planner on the market at any price.  Features include:</H4>
<P></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/btn1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Calendar Screen</BIG></P>
<P>At the center of the action, <B>EuroData</B>'s drag-n-drop <B>Calendar
Screen</B> lets you lay out the what, when, and where of your trip with a few
clicks of the mouse.  Arrange and rearrange dates &amp; destinations, move &amp;
swap cities, create and save as many versions as you like until it's just right.
 Plus, the Calendar will automatically flag national holidays in your
destination countries -- so you don't end up stumbling into crowded trains and
closed attractions. <A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1a.htm">(See me, 16k)</A></P>
<P></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/95exch.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Itinerary Budget</BIG></P>
<P>Wondering how to pay for it all?  The detailed <B>Itinerary Budget</B>
helps you accurately predict costs, including the daily meals &amp;
miscellaneous expenses that many travel planners forget.  <B>EuroData</B>
automatically calculates hotel costs in both local &amp; US currency, even for
multiple rooms at different rates; accounts for travel fares, sleeping car
supplements, booking fees, and more.  To complete the picture, you can enter
virtually unlimited custom budget items, from shopping in Paris to parking at
the airport.  <A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1b.htm">(See me, 21k)</A></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/95ntbk.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Itinerary Notebook</BIG></P>
<P>Things you don't want to miss or forget?  Use the <B>Daily Notes</B> window
and <B>Itinerary Notebook</B> to record those important reminders &amp;
must-see ideas -- day by day and overall.
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1c.htm">(See me, 10k)</A></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/btn7.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Online Capture</BIG></P>
<P>Finding a ton of information on the Internet, CompuServe&#174;, America
Online&#174;, Prodigy&#174;, and other sources?  Losing it as quick as you find
it?  Let <B>EuroData</B>'s <B>Online Capture</B> help you <I>save</I> what
you see and <I>use</I> what you save.  Grab useful notes instantly from almost
any  Windows&#174;-based software -- even travel CDs -- and drop them right into
your travel plans.  Forget that clutter of printouts and obscure 8.3
filenames... let EuroData organize your finds by title and category.  The Format
tool will even remove most HTML codes from captured source text.  Build your own
customized travel guide to print with your itinerary &amp; take along! 
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1d.htm">(See me, 12k)</A></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/bkres.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Bookings &amp; Reservations</BIG></P>
<P>When you're done planning and ready to go, <B>EuroData</B> works from your
itinerary to build detailed <B>Reservation Request</B> documents, ready for
dispatch to your travel agent or direct provider.  Or with
<B>EuroData Connections</B>, booking it
<I>all</I> right from your PC can be as simple as clicking a button.    And if
you're already booking your travel online, use <B>EuroData</B> to pull it all
together and  track your sources, reservations, confirmations, and payments.<A
HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1e.htm">(See me, 13k)</A></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/nsmk2.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Traveler Profile</BIG></P>
<P>Get it done <I>right</I>... EuroData stores all of your personal
preferences, from seating to smoking to frequent flyer numbers, and makes sure
they're included when final plans are made.</P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/printer.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>    
Print Preview</BIG></P>
<P>Finally, input means nothing without output -- and EuroData's slick Print
Preview module not only generates colorful, well-organized reports on every
aspect of your trip, but lets you save them as ASCII files for easy e-mailing to
colleagues or relatives, or envious friends! 
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1f.htm">(See me, 15k)</A></P>
<HR>
<H2><I>Plus, you can use EuroData with these other great products (coming
soon..).</I></H2>
<P></P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/eshop.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG> 
<BIG>
EuroShop</BIG></BIG></P>
<P>Want to work out your plans at your own pace, away from the ever-ticking &quot;online
meter&quot;? <B>EuroData</B> is perfect.  With <B>EuroData</B> and <B>Personal
Programs' EuroShop</B>, you can peruse a wide variety of European travel options
at your leisure with our own
<I>offline</I> browser and compact, quick-download, <B>free</B> database
files.  </P>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/tcrp.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BIG>  
<BIG>Thomas Cook European Railplanner</BIG></BIG></P>
<P>Doing Europe by rail?  Make itinerary design a snap with the
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/tcrp1.htm">Thomas Cook European Railplanner</A>
-- offering schedules, approximate fares, and general information for hundreds
of the most popular European rail routes in a fun, informative Windows
environment.  Easily import routes from <B>Railplanner</B> to your <B>EuroData</B>
itinerary.  And with EuroData Connections, you can buy rail passes, reserve
sleeping cars, even buy <B>Chunnel tickets</B> right from your PC.</P>
<HR>
<P></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/eurodata.htm"><I>Return to Personal
Programs' EuroData Home Page</I></A></P>
