<HTML><HEAD><TITLE></TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><H2>EuroData for Windows</H2>
<P>Frequently Asked Questions, Bug Reports, and Corrections</P>
<HR>
<P><B>Installing the downloadable version: </B> When you download EuroData
from the Internet or an online service, what you receive is a single
self-extracting executable file called ed2wset.exe.  The best way to install
EuroData is to locate your downloaded copy of this file in Windows File Manager
and double-click on it.  EuroData will then install just as if you were
installing from a setup.exe program on a floppy disk.  Once EuroData is
installed, you may delete the ed2wset.exe program (you may wish to save it off
to a floppy first in case you want to re-install EuroData later).</P>
<P><B>Sharing copies of EuroData: </B>It is acceptable to make copies of
EuroData for your friends, but please encourage them to register their copy of
the program separately.  EuroData may <B>not</B> be posted to any bulletin
board, uselist, or online service, or otherwise distributed to the general
public, without express authorization from Personal Programs.  EuroData is a
copyrighted program and is not shareware or in the public domain.</P>
<P><B>Bookings &amp; Purchases: </B>The current version of EuroData   does not
include online booking or purchasing capabilities.   These features will be
included in an add-on program,  EuroData Connections, which should be released
in the first quarter of 1996.  If you register your copy of EuroData for
Windows, you will be notified when EuroData Connections is available.  There
will be no charge for this add-on.  The current version does allow you to
generate and print    Reservation Requests and other reports, and you may fax
these from your computer if your fax software supports faxing as a print option.</P>
<P><B>When installing EuroData under Windows 95</B>, do not place it in a path
which includes a non-Win31 compatible segment (e.g., &quot;c:\Program Files\..&quot;).
 EuroData will fail to resolve this path correctly in internal operations.  All
of our testing indicates that EuroData runs fine under Windows 95 provided it is
placed in a Win31-compatible path (e.g. the default, &quot;c:\ed2w\...&quot;)</P>
<P>At the <B>highest screen resolutions</B> (over 800x600), EuroMap will not
display cities in the correct positions because the background bitmap is too
small.  There is no present workaround for this except to run EuroData at a
lower resolution.</P>
<P><B>Accented Characters:</B> The online Help in some versions mistakenly
says to use an ALT-SHIFT combination to enter accented characters.  The correct
combination is CTRL-SHIFT.</P>
<P><B>Print Preview: </B>With some HP-DeskJet printers, print jobs may take
much longer to generate than with other printers.  During this time the
hourglass cursor may return to normal, giving an impression that nothing is
happening.  We are trying to resolve this problem, which is due to the 2-way
communication (printer-PC) that the HP driver utilizes.  If you are using an
HP-DeskJet, be patient and the print preview screen should appear in 5-10
seconds.
</P>
<P>In EuroData program version 1.0a (12.20.95), a problem occurs with the
Itinerary Report when a <B>car rental</B> is entered with Number of Days = 1. 
The rental will show up on its rental day <EM>and</EM> on each subsequent day
in the Itinerary Report.  Unfortunately the only work-around for this is to
increase the number of rental days to at least 2.  This bug is corrected in
subsequent versions.  If your verson of ed2w.exe has a date of 12.20.95 and you
have encountered this problem, you may want to download the latest version of
the .exe file (see &quot;Updates &amp; Patches&quot; below).</P>
<P><B>Online Capture:</B> A problem may occur if you attempt to use this
feature to capture text from a Windows Help program (including EuroData Online
Help).  Under some circumstances this may cause your system to lock up.  Since
capturing text from a help program would be an unusual use of this feature, you
will probably not experience this problem. 
</P>
<P>In the unlikely event that EuroData for Windows terminates unexpectedly due
to a program error, it's advisable to close all applications and exit Windows
before trying to run EuroData   for Windows again.  Attempting to run EuroData
again without rebooting could cause further problems, including General
Protection Faults.</P>
<P>There are reports of <B>Print Preview</B> causing GPFs under certain
circumstances.  This primarily affects developers who are using the file
VSVIEW.VBX in the Visual Basic development environment.  Because EuroData is a
Visual Basic program, if you have been using VB as a development tool it is
generally advisable to reboot your system prior to running the EuroData
executable.  Print Preview may also encounter problems if you change your screen
resolution after running EuroData and do not fully reboot the system prior to
running it again.</P>
<P><B>Deleting items from the Travel Routes Table:</B>  There is a bug in the
current version of EuroData that prevents deletions from working.  If you need
to remove items from the Travel Routes Table, you can edit the data file
directly using Notepad as it is stored as a plain text file.  Simply locate the
items you want to remove and delete them, then save the file.  Avoid leaving
blank lines where the deletions were, and <B>do not</B> delete any of the
section headings (numbers in brackets, for example &quot;[5]&quot;).</P>
<P><B>Changing the Italian Lira value:</B>  When you make small changes in the
&quot;$1 = nnnn.nnnn Lira&quot; calculation in the Currency Exchange Window it
may appear not to save the change.  This occurs because EuroData actually stores
exchange rates the other way around, i.e. &quot;1 [currency] = $nnnn.nnnn&quot;.
 Because of the Lira's very small unit value, &quot;$1=1550&quot; and &quot;$1=1563&quot;
(for example) both work out to &quot;$0.00064&quot; and this is the value that
is stored.  When you bring it up again, EuroData recalculates the $1=Lira value
(1/.00064) and it appears the same.  The workaround for this is not to worry
about it -- any change less than 20Lit in the rate won't have much impact on
your budget (we're talking 1/1000s of a cent here!).</P>
<P>A utility program, <B>Version Check</B>, has been installed with EuroData.
This program can be used to help identify any version conflicts in Windows
system files if you are having trouble running  EuroData.</P>
<P>Using the <B>UnInstall</B> utility:   An &quot;uninstall&quot; icon has
been added should you wish to remove   EuroData from your computer.  When you
double-click this icon,   an uninstall program will run that removes everything
from your computer than EuroData Setup placed there.  Be very careful  about
deleting system files (with extensions of .vbx or .dll) as these may be used by
other programs.</P>
<HR>
<H2>Updates &amp; Patches</H2>
<P>You can download the latest ed2wset.exe update (2.27.96)
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/edwsetup.exe">here</A> (979kb).   version.) 
Corrections &amp; changes made in the version above include:</P>
<UL><LI>1-day car rental bug is fixed</LI>
<LI>Expanded Travel Routes Table shows more information</LI>
<LI>Notes for Travel Routes and Hotels now appear on report printouts</LI>
<LI>Backspace key now works in Credit Card Password entry</LI>
<LI>Mis-assigned cities on map are corrected (Lugano is back in Switzerland!)</LI>
<LI>Help error about foreign characters is corrected</LI></UL>
<HR>
<P><B>EuroData for DOS Data Import</B></P>
<P>Import Tools are now available for converting hotel &amp; travel route
records from EuroData for DOS to a format usable by EuroData for Windows.  Two
separate programs are required to do this: download 
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed12cv.exe">ED12CV.EXE (Step 1)(191k) here</A>
and
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed12dn.exe">ED12DN.EXE (Step 2)(97k)</A> here.
 The latter program is a self-installing executable which should be run from
within Windows.    If your verson of EuroData for Windows (ed2w.exe) is dated
before 1/7/96, you may also want to download the latest version (see above)
which provides better support for notes in travel route records.  Please note
that only hotel and travel route records can be converted; itineraries created
in EuroData for DOS cannot be converted for use in EuroData for Windows.</P></BODY></HTML>
