<HEAD>
<TITLE>European Visits: Favorites</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#80FFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#800000">
<P><EM>European Visits: A Newsletter of European Travel</EM></P>
<P><EM><FONT COLOR="#FF0080">September / October 1996</FONT></EM></P>
<HR>
<H1>What&#146;s Your Favorite?</H1>
<P><I><B>European Visits</B></I> invites you to tell us about your favorite
European <B>anything!</B>  Favorite travel story?  Favorite hotel?  Restaurant?
 Rail trip?  Museum?  Castle?  Walking tour?  Pastry?  Public square?  Reason
for going to Europe?  Nothing fancy is required -- just put it in your own words
(250 to 1500 of them) and we&#146;ll take it from there.  Send it along by email
to <A HREF="mailto:eurodata@nas.com">eurodata@nas.com</A> with &#147;Readers
Write&#148; in the subject line, or by postal mail to <B>European Visits, 4718
Neptune Circle, Ferndale, WA 98248</B>.  Include the what-when-where-who-how
much details whenever possible.  If we use your tale in EV, you&#146;ll receive
your choice of one of our splendid &#147;I&#146;d rather be in Europe...&#148;
mouse pads, aprons, or sweatshirts (see
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ratherb">here</A>), or a free copy of the
latest edition of the <I>Thomas Cook European Timetable</I>.  (Indicate choice
with your letter.)  And we&#146;ll also add your name to our semi-annual drawing
for a <B>First Class, 15 Day Eurail Pass!</B>     We look forward to hearing
from you -- and so do your fellow travelers. 
</P>
<HR>
