<HR>
<H2>Finally, reliable European rail information for your PC!</H2>
<HR>
<P>The <B>Railplanner</B> brings schedules, approximate fares, and useful
information for hundreds of intercity European rail routes into a fun,
easy-to-use Windows environment.  Includes routes for the new &quot;Chunnel&quot;
trains between Britain and the Continent, as well as Eastern Europe and Russia.
 <STRONG>Terrific for working out railpass trips! </STRONG> You can easily
import Railplanner routes into your
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/ed2w1.htm">EuroData</A>  itinerary... and with
<B>EuroData Connections</B>, you can even purchase railpasses or make
reservation requests right from your computer.  Developed by Personal Programs
in cooperation with Thomas Cook Publishing (UK), the <B>European Railplanner</B>
is a perfect PC companion to their famous
<A HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/tcookbk.htm">European Timetable</A>.  Updates
available on disk or online.  Estimated MSRP $29.95.  <I>Available 1st Quarter
1996.</I></P> 
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/cook1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE">	    Visit
<A HREF="http://www.thomascook.com/">Thomas Cook</A> on the World Wide Web</P>
