<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>European Visits: Traveler's News Stand</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#80FFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#800000">
<P><EM><STRONG>European Visits:</STRONG> A Newsletter of European Travel</EM></P>
<P><EM>July / August 1996</EM></P>
<HR>
<H1><FONT COLOR="#004080">Traveler's News Stand</FONT></H1>
<HR>
<P><EM><STRONG><FONT COLOR="#FF0080">About 20% of our survey respondents
name France as their favorite destination.  If you're among them, there are a 
number of specialty publications available that you may find of interest.  Some
titles we've come across lately:</FONT></STRONG></EM><BR></P>
<P><B><I>&#183; France Today</I></B></P>
<P>This bi-monthly tabloid size newspaper offers travel tips, regional
profiles, restaurant &amp; hotel notes, book reviews, and cultural essays on
France and French travel.  In English. $35 per year for six issues.</P>
<P><I>France Today</I>, PO Box 1522, Martinez, CA 94553; 1-800-851-7785</P>
<HR>
<P><B><I>&#183; Journal Fran&ccedil;ais</I></B></P>
<P>From the same publisher, a journal aimed at serious Francophiles, providing &quot;sociocultural
and political highlights...opinion polls...updates on the economy...the hottest
trends and enduring traditions...tips on travel and tourism...sporting
events...the arts...and much more.&quot;  In French.  $35 for 24 issues per
year.</P>
<P><I>Journal Fran&ccedil;ais</I>, PO Box 1522, Martinez, CA 94553;
1-800-851-7785</P>
<HR>
<P><B><I>&#183; La Belle France</I></B></P>
<P>Calling itself the &quot;sophisticated guide to France&quot;, <I>La Belle
France</I> carries no advertising and is strongly focused on upscale hotel and
restaurant reviews, along with some brief destination pieces, in a newsletter
format.  Well-written though perhaps a bit thin (8 pages) for the price.  In
English.  $87 per year (but frequent trial offers at $49).<BR></P>
<P><I>La Belle France</I>, Travel Guide Inc., PO Box 3485, Charlottesville, VA
22903; 1-800-851-7785</P>
<HR>
<P><B><I>&#183; Paris Notes</I></B></P>
<P>If your interests center more on the City of Lights, this newsletter will
bring Paris to your mailbox every month with feature articles, historical
anecdotes, shopping guides, and a calendar of upcoming events.  In English.  $39
per year.<BR></P>
<P><I>Paris Notes</I>, PO Box 3668, Manhattan Beach, CA 90266 (no phone given)</P>
<HR>
<P><B><I>&#183; Champs-Elys&eacute;es</I></B></P>
<P>Aimed at both beginners seeking to learn French and bi-linguists who wish to
improve their skills, each issue of this unique &quot;radio magazine&quot;
includes an audiocassette, a booklet containing a transcript and extensive
glossary, and an optional study supplement that helps you put the tape &amp;
booklet to best use with a series of exercises geared to various levels of
expertise.  The content -- presented by Georges Lang, one of France's most
popular radio &amp; TV personalities -- includes book reviews, profiles of
historic places, events in the news, and interviews with prominent French
writers and performers. In French and English.  5 issues for $79 or 11 issues (1
year) for $129; study supplements extra.</P>
<P><I>Champs-Elys&eacute;es</I>,  PO Box 158067, Nashville TN 37215-8067; 
1-800-824-0829</P>
<HR>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT SIZE="-1">Articles appearing on this page are &copy;1996
Personal Programs and/or the contributor.  All rights reserved.  Opinions
expressed are those of the writer(s). Travel information is by nature subject to
frequent change; travelers should always verify information prior to relying
upon it.  Personal Programs does not represent and does not endorse products,
companies, or offers referenced on this page, and cannot be responsible for
errors, changes, or omissions.  Please send comments to Personal Programs at
<A HREF="mailto:eurodata@nas.com">eurodata@nas.com</A></FONT>. </P>
