<TITLE>European Visits: A Newsletter of European Travel - Check It Out / Travel
Bargain / Special Travel Offers / Discount Travel / New Travel Products /
Stories about Europe / Online Magazine / Travel in Europe</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#000080" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#C0DCC0"><IMG
SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evlogo.gif">
<HR>
<H2><I><B><FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">Check It Out</FONT></B></I></H2>
<P><I><B>Best Buys, New Products, and Intriguing Offers in European Travel</B></I><BR></P>
<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">We regularly comb the marketplace to see what's on
tap for European travelers, and in each issue of European Visits we'll list some
the better bargains or more unusual offerings here in the Check It Out pages. 
Keep in mind that prices and availability are always subject to change.   And if
you find something of interest, do us a favor -- <B>tell them you saw it in
European Visits!    
</B></FONT></P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P><B>Eurail Pass</B> prices will <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">hold steady</FONT>
next year, according to <B>Rail Europe</B>.  The less expensive Europass, which
offers travel on a certain number of days for a subset of countries, will go up
in cost but will also have <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">expanded benefits</FONT>,
allowing travel in all five base countries (<B>France</B>, <B>Germany</B>,
<B>Italy</B>, <B>Spain</B>, and <B>Switzerland</B>) on 5 to 15 days over a
two-month period.  (With the current version of Europass you can only select 3
or 4 of these countries, and the period of use is shorter.)  Another improvement
is that <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">Hungary will be included</FONT> on the list of
countries you can add to a Europass for an extra charge; Austria, Belgium, the
<B>Netherlands</B>, <B>Luxembourg</B>, <B>Greece</B>, and <B>Portugal</B>
are the presently available add-ons.  For more information contact your favorite
rail agent, or Rail Europe at <B>800-4EURAIL</B>.  </P><IMG
SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P>Through December, your <B>European rail pass </B>can save you<FONT
COLOR="#FFFF00"> big bucks</FONT> at many <B>Hilton Hotels</B> in Europe; a
number of their properties are offering 30% to 40% discounts for pass holders. 
Call <B>800-HILTONS</B> for details.  
</P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P><B>Perillo Tours</B>, longtime operators of escorted travel packages to
<B>Italy</B> (and elsewhere), is offering an 11-day tour with visits to <B>Rome</B>
(3 nights) <B>Florence</B> (3) <B>Venice</B> (2) and <B>Milan</B> (1), plus
dinner every night in each city's finer restaurants, from $1799 PP/DO; good
through next spring.  A special touch from Perillo is that their tours are
<FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">priced the same from any of 50 U.S. cities</FONT>
coast-to-coast; with most tours, airfare to the East Coast is extra.  You can
visit Perillo and learn more about them &amp; their specials at
www.perillotours.com; or call <B>800-431-1515</B>.  
</P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P>Another source of value-priced packages to <B>Italy</B> is <B>TourCrafters</B>,
with a variety of products from fully-inclusive escorted tours to &quot;hosted&quot;
visits (in which you're mainly on your own but with access to a TourCrafters rep
for advice or special requests).  They specialize in providing<FONT
COLOR="#FFFF00"> hotels &quot;in the historic city centre&quot;</FONT> of their
destinations, which also include <B>Greece</B>, <B>Turkey</B>, <B>Budapest</B>,
<B>Prague</B>, and <B>Vienna</B>.   TourCrafters, <B>800-621-2259</B>.  
</P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P>If you'd like a humorous take on visiting <B>Russia</B>, including a ride
on the Trans-Siberian Express, check out the latest issue of <I>Rolling Stone</I>;
it features a <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">hilarious</FONT> (sometimes savage) essay
from conservative satirist <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">PJ O'Rourke</FONT>, detailing
his most recent visit to the former Worker's Paradise.  <I>At newstands.  
</I></P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P>Want to travel with a group but <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">hate motorcoaches</FONT>?
 <B>Europe Train Tours</B> may be your answer.  They offer fully-inclusive and
escorted train trips throughout Europe, including the famous Glacier Express
from <B>St. Moritz</B> to <B>Zermatt</B>.  They can also take you along on the
deluxe <B>Venice-Simplon-Orient-Express</B>, on mountainous journeys through
the spectacular <B>Austrian Alps</B>, and numerous other places.  ETT can
arrange <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">independent train travel</FONT> too, with
packages to <B>Switzerland</B>, <B>Austria</B>, <B>France</B> and <B>Italy</B>.
<B>800-551-2085</B>.  
</P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P>Add this nugget to <B>Susan Milligan</B>'s article <I><A
HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/paris1.htm">Paris on the Cheap</A></I>:  in a
special aimed at student travelers, <B>New Frontiers</B> is offering airfares
NYC-Paris from $219 O/W, and rooms in <B>Paris</B> from $22/night per person. 
Rates are based on <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">four people</FONT> traveling &amp;
rooming together.  <B>800-366-6387</B>.  <I>(Note: we ran this Check It Out
item last issue, but Susan's article ended up getting postponed to this one. 
So, we don't mind repeating ourselves in a good cause.)  
</I></P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P><B>DER Travel Services</B> is touting weekly <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">Mercedes
rentals</FONT> in Europe for as little as $37 a day.  You can pick up in <B>Frankfurt</B>,
<B>Munich</B>, or <B>Vienna</B> and go just about anywhere you want; bring the
car back to <B>Vienna</B> or any dropoff point in <B>Germany</B> without extra
charges.  <B>800-782-2424</B>.  
</P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/evline.gif">
<P>It's easier than ever to add a <B>Brussels</B> visit to your schedule,
using the new<FONT COLOR="#FFFF00"> high-speed </FONT><I>Thalys</I> rail
service from Paris.  The added TGV line&#151;an offshoot of services put in
place for the Eurostar trains&#151;can now whisk you from <B>Paris</B> Nord to
<B>Brussels</B> Midi, or back again, in just <FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">two hours</FONT>.
 Make reservations with Rail Europe, <B>800-4EURAIL</B>.  
