<H1>The Thomas Cook European Timetable</H1>
<H4>This venerable compendium of European railway schedules, services, and
general information just gets better every year.  If you're planning to &quot;do
Europe&quot; by rail, leaving without the Thomas Cook European Timetable in your
kit is like leaving without your tickets. </H4>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>&quot;The only readily available guide to European rail
services.   Tables  updated monthly.  Featuring all  major and most minor
services.&quot; -- Thomas Cook Publishing</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.eurodata.com/cook1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></P>
<P><BIG>Visit
<A HREF="http://www.thomascook.com/">Thomas Cook</A> on the World Wide Web to
learn more about their wide range of publications &amp; travel services.
</BIG></P>
<P> <BIG>To order a copy of the Thomas Cook European Timetable in the U.S. or
Canada, call <STRONG>Forsyth Travel Library</STRONG></BIG> <BIG>at <STRONG>1-800-367-7984</STRONG>.
 You can also visit Forsyth on the Web at <A HREF="http://www.forsyth.com/">http://www.forsyth.com</A>.</BIG></P>
