<HTML><HEAD><TITLE></TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><P><I>European Visits: A Newsletter of European Travel</I></P>
<H1>The Online Traveler</H1>
<HR>
<H2><B><I>Selected Online European Travel Resources</I></B></H2>
<P>The Internet is filled with terrific travel resources, and more are being
added every day.  Some current picks include:</P>
<P><B>Tra<I>Velocity</I> Debut!</B>  It's up, it's open, and it's <B>huge</B>
-- the new online travel venture from Sabre and Worldview, long-time industry
leaders in travel technology, has gone live on the World Wide Web.  They are
reputed to have more than <I>two hundred thousand pages</I> of Web data for
destinations around the globe.  Online reservations and electronic travel
merchandise shopping are available along with a wealth of information. Visit at
<A HREF="http://www.travelocity.com/">http://www.travelocity.com</A>.<BR></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.goeurope.com/index.html"><B>Go Europe!</B></A> at the
<B>European Travel</B> <B>Commission</B>'s new, beautifully designed Web site.
 Lots of destination information and links to the home pages of European tourist
agencies, plus a
<B>Travelers' Forum</B> where you can read postings from fellow travelers on
hotels, restaurants, and more.  The have a <B>sweepstakes</B> going on too,
with various prizes.  Take a look!<BR></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.travel.org/"><B>Travel Org </B></A> is a terrific site
which plays host to home pages for a variety of destinations.  Click your way to
a vast collection of sites for Britain, France, Italy, Greece, just about
anywhere in Europe.  Don't miss this one if you're building your set of travel
bookmarks.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.interport.net/cellular/ew.html"><B>Cruise the
waterways of Europe.</B>  </A>  Indulge your guests aboard a private boat
complete with captain, crew, and chef.  <B>EUROPEAN WATERWAYS</B></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.interport.net/cellular/orion.html"><B>European
apartment living</B></A>  for as long as you like.  Great for families! 
Locations close to business, cultural, and recreational centers.  <B>RESIDENCES
ORION</B></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.interport.net/cellular"><B>Cellular phones for
international travelers.</B></A>  Reserve before departure; your phone will be
there when you arrive!  Available throughout Europe, Asia, and Africa. <B>WORLD
CELLULAR SERVICE</B></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.raileurope.com/"><B>Rail Europe </B>Home Page</A>. 
Lots of information on European rail, including fares and services.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/misc/uk/london/museums.html"><B>Museums
in London</B></A>.  Great page to check out if you're heading to Jolly Old
London.  Addresses, phone numbers, hours of operation, etc. for a wide range of
London museums, including some off-the-wall places you may not know about.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.webfoot.com/travel/guides/france"><B>The Webfoot's
Guide to France</B></A>.  Must-see page for the France-bound.  A very large
collection of French travel resources.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.eurail.com/"><B>Rail Pass Express</B></A>  Rail
services and information from the publishers of <B><I>Europe by Eurail</I></B>
and <B><I>Britain by Britrail</I></B></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.enews.com/travel/ehi/"><B>European Horizons, Inc.</B></A>
 From the publishers of the <B><I>Europe At Your Fingertips</I></B> guides
relied on by many travel agents.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.enews.com/magazines/travel_h"><B>Travel Holiday
Magazine</B></A>.  One of the first &amp; best online travel magazines.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.starnetinc.com/eurorail/eurostar.htm">Channel Tunnel,
<B>Eurostar</B> - London / Paris and London / Brussels train service</A>. 
Everything you want to know about the new under-Channel trains.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.starnetinc.com/eurorail/home.htm"><B>On Line Travel
</B>Home Page</A>.  One of the pioneers of online travel information.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.travelweb.com/"><B>TravelWeb</B></A>.  Home to Best
Western and Hyatt Hotels' home pages, among many others.  Lots of hotel
information.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.lonelyplanet.com/"><B>Lonely Planet</B> Online</A>. 
Maybe the best collection of travel information pages on the Web.  Very good
<I>current</I> data.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://bin.gnn.com/cgi-bin/gnn/currency/">The GNN/Koblas <B>Currency
Converter </B></A> will perform exchange calculations for almost any two
currencies.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.uktw.co.uk/">UK <B>Theatre </B>Web </A> offers
up-to-date info on what's playing the West End &amp; other theatres in London.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.traveler.net/"><B>Travel Weekly</B>'s Home Page </A>. 
Home page of the travel industry's newspaper.  Lots of good links &amp; general
travel news.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.demon.co.uk/hotel-uk">HOTEL-UK</A>, The UK <B>On-Line
Reservations</B> System</P> 
<P><BR></P>
