<H2><I><FONT COLOR="#FFFF00">Letters</FONT></I></H2>
<P></P>
<P>&#164; <B>Thank you</B>, and thank you for no photos [in the Internet
edition].  I waste so much time and money with graphics and those of us
interested in travel probably have spent a lot of time looking at beautiful
pictures previously.   The Albanian article was concise, informative and just
what I have been looking for for years.  When we moved to Chicago in 1979, an
ultra-left group was plastering the city with handbills asking us to join the
revolutionary Albanian movement.   There is an Albanian community here I believe&#151;the
Belushi family is sometimes mentioned as part of it&#151;but these folks were
coming from somewhere else!  Thanks for a real life look at this newly available
country.  	<BR>-- Carroll
</P>
<P><B>&#164; I'm visiting your site for the first time today</B> and enjoying
it immensely.  The articles are not only informative but extremely well written.
I am a specialty travel planner for upscale, leisure travel.  I can never have
too many resources!  Thanks!  										<BR>--Carolyn Patterson</P>
<P><B>&#164; I do enjoy your magazine</B>&#151;it's the most informative one
I've found online for places I have visited and plan to visit.  The article on
London and the area along the Thames was excellent. I printed it out and used it
while I was in London. It was accurate and I appreciate the information supplied
by the author, Jerri Clark Kirby.  Keep up the good work!   			<BR>	--Jim
Zattiero 
