<P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0080">Welcome to the 4th issue of <I>European Visits</I>.</FONT>
Once again we have a great set of articles from both new and returning writers;
and we have a couple of submissions for our Readers Write section, in which the
authors share with us their British experiences in pubs and tennis.  As always,
we hope you'll enjoy the issue and invite you to write to us if you have
comments or suggestions -- or better yet, tales of your own to tell.  (Take a
look at our contributor guidelines at <B><A
HREF="http://www.eurodata.com/evsubmit.htm">http://www.eurodata.com/submit.htm</A>)</B></B>
 </P>
<P>You can reach us at <B><A HREF="mailto:eurodata@nas.com">eurodata@nas.com</A></B>,
or by postal mail to <B>European Visits, 4718 Neptune Circle, Ferndale, WA
98248</B>.  Please write -- the magazine's for you, and we want to know what you
think.</P>
<P> Scott Peterson, Editor, <I><B>European Visits</B></I></P>
