<HEAD>
<TITLE>European Visits: Check It Out</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#80FFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#800000">
<P><EM><STRONG>European Visits:</STRONG> A Newsletter of European Travel</EM></P>
<P><EM>July / August 1996</EM></P>
<HR>
<H1><FONT COLOR="#004080">Check It Out!</FONT></H1>
<HR>
<P><STRONG><EM><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="#FF0080">Best Buys, New Products, &amp;
Intriguing Offers in European Travel</FONT></EM></STRONG><BR><EM>We regularly
comb the marketplace to see what's on tap for European travelers, and in each
issue of European Visits we'll list some the better bargains or more unusual
offerings here in the Check It Out pages.  Keep in mind that prices and
availability are always subject to change.  However, we do our best to check
what we publish, and everything listed here was available as EV went to press. 
If you find something of interest, do us a favor -- tell them you saw it in
<STRONG><FONT COLOR="#004080">European Visits</FONT></STRONG></EM>!</P>
<HR>
<UL>
<LI>For those who want to try the leisurely on-foot pace, but aren't power
hikers, <STRONG><EM>Walking Easy in the Italian Alps</EM></STRONG> gives
offers some of the ins and outs.  The book is $11.95; call <STRONG>800-669-0773</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>Another pedestrian approach comes from London Walks, a group that organizes
guided walking tours around <STRONG>London</STRONG>'s  historic streets.  Their
guides include an author who is internationally recognised as the leading
authority on Jack the Ripper, a distinguished BBC broadcaster and writer, and a
London archaeologist among others.  No need to book ahead; you just show up at
the appropriate spot and join the group.  Tours are &#163;4, with discounts
available if you take several different tours.  Contact <STRONG>London Walks</STRONG>
at PO Box 1708 London, NW6 4LW; Tel. 0171 624 3978, fax 0171 625 1932.  They're
also on the Web with complete tour details, at
<A HREF="http://scim.co.uk/londonwalks">http://scim.co.uk/londonwalks</A>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>Vantage Deluxe World Travel</STRONG> offers a variety of European
fully escorted tours; one scheduled for April 1997 offers eight days visiting
Counties Galway and Killarney in <STRONG>Ireland</STRONG>, plus 3 days in
Dublin; everything including air from New York is covered for $2999 PP/DO.  Add
$180-$200 for other departure cities.  <STRONG>800-322-6677</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>Forsyth Travel Library</STRONG>  has moved: their new address is
1750 E. 131st Street, PO Box 480800, Kansas City, MO 64148.  Their toll free
number (<B>800-367-7984</B>) remains the same.  FTL are specialists in European
rail products, and are exclusive US distributors of the essential <STRONG><EM>Thomas
Cook European Timetable</EM></STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>If the main thing you're packing along to take to Europe is your appetite,
you'll also want to pack Frommer's new <STRONG><EM>Food Lover's Companion</EM></STRONG>
books.  Publisher Macmillian has launched this series with an edition for France
and another for Italy; the books focus on travel from a diner's point of view,
with in-depth restaurant guides, exploration of local delicacies, and advice on
how to shop for picnics or preparing your own fine foods.  <STRONG>$19.95</STRONG>
at your travel bookstore.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>Also on the food front, <B>Taylor Made Travel</B> is offering an Irish
culinary tour this fall from September 29 to October 9.  The escorted tour
includes dining at some of <STRONG>Ireland</STRONG>'s finest restaurants, as
well as a visit to the 20th annual Gourmet Festival in Kinsale, a whisky
tasting, and a cooking demonstration at the Ballymaloe Cooking School.  Land
only price for the deluxe tour is $3475 pp/do; space is strictly limited, and
must be booked by travel agents; ask your agent to call Taylor Made Travel at
<B>800-653-8808</B>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>If you'd prefer an emphasis on liquid refreshments, European specialists<STRONG>MIR
Corp</STRONG>. have two September tours that will interest you: <EM>Artisan
Breweries of <STRONG>Holland</STRONG> &amp;
<STRONG>Belgium</STRONG></EM> departs Sept. 10 for 10 days, and <EM>Fine Beers
&amp; Wines of <STRONG>Czech</STRONG> and <STRONG>Hungary</STRONG></EM> goes
Sept. 12 for 9 days.  In October, they're doing <I>Brewing Traditions of
<STRONG>England</STRONG> &amp; <STRONG>Scotland</STRONG></I>.  Land only
packages run $1295 and up.  MIR are also known for their expertise in Eastern
Europe, and have a number of <STRONG>Russian</STRONG> and Central Asian tours
scheduled.  MIR Corporation, <STRONG>800-424-7289</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>AutoNet International</STRONG> has a special that gives you 7
Novotel vouchers for the price of 6 when you rent a car for a week; they have
620 locations in 27 countries and will let you prepay for guaranteed exchange
rates.  <STRONG>800-221-3465</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>Worldwide Vacations</STRONG>' Europe for the Asking program
includes a package deal with 6 nights' hotel in <STRONG>Malta</STRONG>, plus
r/t air from New York, for just $999 pp/do. <STRONG> 800-841-8222</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>With such a wide array of tours available, it can be hard to find the deal
that really suits you; even a dedicated travel agent can only cover so many
options, and you're left wondering what else might be out there.  To the rescue
comes <STRONG>Tours to Go!</STRONG>, a new company that maintains a vast
database of available tours and specializes in matching the interests and
budgets of individual travelers to the right packages.  For more information,
phone Tours to Go! at <B>770 503 0340</B>, or contact them by e-mail at
<A HREF="mailto:Rlove333@gnn.com">Rlove333@gnn.com</A>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>Tradesco Tours</STRONG> can set you up with first-class lodging in
<STRONG>Vienna</STRONG> for three nights, including buffet breakfast and taxes,
starting at $219 pp/do.  Add tickets to two major cultural attractions -- such
as Vienna State Opera, Vienna Boys' Choir, or a Mozart concert in Schonbrunn
Palace -- for about $220 more.  You can also get a <STRONG>3-day Vienna Card</STRONG>,
good for free local transit and discounted admission at numerous sights around
the city, for just $19 when you book 3 nights' hotel accommodations.  Ask your
travel agent to call Tradesco at <STRONG>800-833-3402</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>Paul Laifer Tours</STRONG> has a package with 3 nights each in
<STRONG>Vienna</STRONG>, <STRONG>Prague</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Budapest</STRONG>;
prices including air from New York and city-to-city transportation start at
$1799 per person.  <STRONG>800-346-6314</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>Ever stared into the museum case, fascinated with those ancient, mysterious
coins and medallions -- and wondered fleetingly if they'd really mind your
taking just one along for a souvenir?  Well, don't get yourself arrested;
<STRONG>Worldwide Treasure Bureau</STRONG> offers a unique catalog of genuine
<STRONG>Greek</STRONG>, <STRONG>Roman</STRONG>, and <STRONG>medieval</STRONG>
coins that you really can claim as your own.  While some of their items are as
costly as you  might expect  (a gold Ferdinand &amp; Isabella double excelente,
c. 1479, is $5,750), others are surprisingly affordable:  in the latest mailing
they have a few coins from the Byzantine era at just $85 each, and some from
medieval Venice for $295 per piece.  Call for a catalog, <STRONG>800 437 0222</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>TWA</STRONG> and <STRONG>Sprint</STRONG> have upped the ante in
the long distance / frequent flyer marketing fray:  if you switch residential
service to Sprint and spend at least $45 per month for a year, you'll end up
with <STRONG>10,000 free TWA FFB points</STRONG>    that's half the level of a
free domestic coach trip.  Offer expires September 30.  Call Sprint,
<STRONG>800-303-1263</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>Until September 7, you can stay in a <STRONG>Holiday Inn</STRONG> in
<STRONG>Paris</STRONG>, <STRONG>Rome</STRONG>, <STRONG>Amsterdam</STRONG>, or
<STRONG>London</STRONG> for no more than $129 per night; in smaller cities (<STRONG>Florence</STRONG>,
<STRONG>Athens</STRONG>, <STRONG>Brussels</STRONG>, etc.) the top rate is $99.
 Space is limited.  <STRONG>800 465 4329</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>Turkish prisoners never had it so good!  A new <STRONG>Four Seasons Hotel</STRONG>,
opening in <STRONG>Istanbul</STRONG> this August, is housed in a renovated
19th-century prison.  The deluxe digs will go for $225 and up per night, double.
 <STRONG>800 332 3442</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>The <STRONG>British Tourist Authority </STRONG>(BTA) offers a guide to
more than 3,000 small hotels, guesthouses, B&amp;Bs, and farmhouses throughout
<STRONG>Britain</STRONG> for just $16.95; it's compiled by the Automobile
Association (the Brit version of our AAA).  They have a variety of other lodging
guides available too.  BTA, <STRONG>800-677-8585</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>In a new twist on the &quot;buy-and-drive&quot; programs that have been
popular in Europe for years, <STRONG>Volvo Export</STRONG> will loan you a
Volvo to drive over there, then ship a brand-new car to you Stateside upon your
return.  Write <STRONG>Volvo Export, Freepost 30, Hatfield, Hertfordshire, AL9
7AR England</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>A complete guide on what to do and where to stay in <STRONG>Dorset</STRONG>
and <STRONG>Wessex</STRONG> is available free from <STRONG>Dorset Tourism,
20-22 Christchurch Road, Bournemouth, Dorset, BH1 3NL</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>The<STRONG> London White Card</STRONG> is a must-have if you're visiting
England's capital.  The card, available in 3-day (&#163;15) and 7 day (&#163;25)
versions, gives you free entry to a long list of the best galleries and museums
in London.  Ask your travel agent or contact the BritRail Travel Bookshop,
<STRONG>212-490-6688</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
