hundreds of detailed listings; they can arrange bookings too.  <STRONG>800-771-4771</STRONG>,
or visit their Web site at
<A HREF="http://www.travelx.com/metaVoya.html">www.travelsource.com/europe/metavoyage.html</A>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI><STRONG>Rail Europe</STRONG> has greatly expanded their operation, and are
now offering airfares and complete packages in addition to their extensive line
of <STRONG>European</STRONG> and <STRONG>British</STRONG> rail products.  They
can also help you with car rentals and <STRONG>Best Western hotel vouchers</STRONG>,
good for lodging for as little as $60 double in more than 800 independently
operated hotels across Europe.  There are a number of specials available on rail
passes this summer and autumn: for example 50% off a companion pass for Swiss
Passes, or <STRONG>33% off Eurostar tickets</STRONG> when you buy a Eurail
Pass, Europass, France Railpass, or Benelux Tourrail Pass.  Another new addition
is their automated fax line, which will send you a detailed fax on schedules and
services after you select your departure and destination points via a touch-tone
menu. <STRONG>800-438 7245</STRONG>.<BR><BR></LI>
<LI>The cities of <STRONG>Bath</STRONG>, <STRONG>York</STRONG>, and <STRONG>Edinburgh</STRONG>
are joining forces to offer a coupon book containing savings on restaurants,
